"n.违法 【英】 n.违法(violation; infringement) 【记】 in(使)+fract(破裂)+ ion→使法律破裂→违法 【同】 同根词：refractory( 倔强的); fraction(碎片) 【例】 We do not condone or tolerate an infraction of even the most trivial kind. n. 违法(法律等) = violation = infringement 【根】fract破裂－使法律破裂－违法 【参】refractory(adj 难控制的; 难熔的); fraction(n 小部份; 片断) 【记】in 不好的 + fraction(break 打破，违犯)，break the law 【相关】fraction 小部份, 片断, 分数 infraction (n.)  mid-15c., ""the breaking of an agreement,"" from Middle French infraction and directly from Latin infractionem (nominative infractio) ""a breaking, weakening,"" noun of action from past participle stem of infringere (see infringe)."
